{{DISPLAYTITLE:&nbsp;}}

<center>
<span style="font-family:Avenir; font-size:96px; background: linear-gradient(180deg, #FFFFFF, #FFFFFF); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; text-shadow: #E30B5C 0px 0px 4px; color:#E30B5C;">Level 882</span>
<br>
<span style="font-family:Avenir; font-size:96px; background: linear-gradient(180deg, #FFFFFF, #FFFFFF); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; text-shadow: #E30B5C 0px 0px 4px; color:#E30B5C;">Grass Mausoleum</span>
</center>

<div style="font-family:Avenir; background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25); border:3px solid #D96CBE; box-shadow: 0px 0px 7px #C8509B; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em">
<center>
<div style="font-family:Avenir; background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25); border:3px solid #D96CBE; box-shadow: 0px 0px 7px #C8509B; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em">
''"I awaken in an unfamiliar realm, hazy and dreamlike. Verdant grass glistens around me, and as I gather my senses, an instinct stirs — to move forward, to wrap myself in the stillness of the meadow, bathed in the glow of a luminous moon..."''
</div>
{{Class Ψ}}
Level 882 is recognized as the 883<sup>rd</sup> documented level within the Backrooms. It was recently uncovered by agents of the M.E.G. (Major Explorer Group) during a field expedition. To date, the level remains highly enigmatic and anomalous in nature, with limited verifiable data available due to the instability of its environment and the psychological effects it imposes on explorers. 

<div style="font-family:Avenir; background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25); border:3px solid #D96CBE; box-shadow: 0px 0px 7px #C8509B; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em">
''"I don’t recall how I arrived — only that I was walking towards an office building… now my thoughts hum and flicker. The stars look down, mocking my fading memory, and I sense that who I was has dissolved among the blades of grass. What choice remains? I must keep moving, weaving my path through these rolling green hills…"''
</div>

{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
=<div style="font-family:Avenir; text-align: center;"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">'''Description'''</span></div>=
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}

Level 882 has been described by those who have encountered it as "majestic," "mesmerizing," and "perfect." The level is composed of multiple distinct zones and architectural features, each contributing to the surreal landscape perceived upon arrival. Despite its apparent beauty, entry into Level 882 is strongly discouraged without direct authorization, as its anomalous psychic effects and undefined properties pose significant risks to both mental stability and physical safety.

The known regions within Level 882, identified through limited exploration, are as follows:

{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
=<div style="font-family:Avenir; text-align: center;"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">'''The Grass'''</span></div>=
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
<div style="font-family:Avenir; background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25); border:3px solid #D96CBE; box-shadow: 0px 0px 7px #C8509B; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em">
''"The indigo sky is strewn with stars — a dawn that never ends. It makes no sense, yet there’s beauty in it, a warmth that softens the heart. As I begin to blend and <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''a m a l g a m a t e'''</span> with the surroundings…”''
</div>

The Grass is the initial area where one appears upon entering Level 882. It features an expanse of seemingly endless hills blanketed in grass, varying in size from modest three-meter mounds to vast formations survivors have described as “<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''t h e s i z e o f a n e x p a n d i n g m i n d'''</span>” — a phenomenon attributed to the profound psychic effects exerted by the level itself.
{{Blurimage|file=Starry field 2 level 882.jpg|caption=A photograph of The Grass, captured by a [[M.E.G.|M.E.G]]. explorer, depicts a solitary hill blanketed in verdant grass beneath a star-filled sky. The scene is bathed in the soft, orange glow of the level’s perpetual dawn, casting an otherworldly light across the landscape.}}

Within the hills, there are noticeable bulging formations that release a greenish, viscous liquid from small geyser-like openings. While the eruptions are not very tall, it is important to keep a safe distance. This liquid is believed to be associated with [[Object 12|Liquid Pain]]. Therefore, it is strongly advised <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''<s>t o t a s t e t h e b r e w i n g o f s t a r s</s>'''</span> not to approach these geysers or come into contact with their contents.

The grass in this region produces a range of psychological effects upon physical contact. At first, individuals report a deep sense of peace and euphoria. This gradually intensifies until <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica">'''<s>t h e i r m i n d s w i l l e x p a n d w i t h t h e c a r e o f t h e s k y</s>'''</span>, leading to sensations often described as “enlightenment.” However, this state is short-lived; it typically gives way to paranoia, anxiety, and severe emotional instability. For safety, it is strongly advised not to remain in contact with The Grass for more than one hour, as this marks the threshold when adverse effects tend to fully emerge.


{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
=<div style="font-family:Avenir; text-align: center;"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">'''The Golden Castle'''</span></div>=
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
<div style="font-family:Avenir; background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25); border:3px solid #D96CBE; box-shadow: 0px 0px 7px #C8509B; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em">
''"A golden castle rises before me… radiant, perhaps truly forged of gold. Yet it’s not the structure that calls — it is a <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''d i v i n i t y —'''</span> I feel its presence growing with every step. It summons me; I must go on. I’ve come too far to turn back now. As I approach, its vastness overwhelms me. Immense — colossal! Its towers pierce the endless dawn, reaching into the heavens… or is it the heavens reaching for them? I can no longer tell…"''
</div>
{{Blurimage|file=The castle wall 882.jpg|caption=A photograph of the Golden Castle’s outer wall reveals bricks composed of orpiment interlaced with five unidentified metallic elements. These materials emit a soft, continuous glow through mechanisms that remain unexplained.|align=left}}
After journeying an uncertain distance, wanderers may eventually reach The Golden Castle. Though its walls shimmer like pure gold, they are in fact constructed from orpiment — a toxic yellow-orange mineral — combined with various unidentified metals <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif"><s>'''b u t l e t y o u r s e l f a t o n e b y b e a u t y'''.</s></span> The full scale of the castle remains unknown, as it seems to extend across the entirety of The Grass, blending seamlessly with the terrain . 

Two towers remain constantly visible at the periphery of one’s vision. These structures rise endlessly into the sky, and any attempt to view them in their entirety results in severe migraines and visual distortion. Though undeniably striking, direct observation is strongly discouraged. Apart from these anomalous spires, the main body of the castle reaches an estimated height of 300 meters. 

Engravings are etched along the castle walls, their patterns intricate and ancient. Some of the inscriptions read: 

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">* '''l e t  t h e  p a r a d i s e  f i l l  y o u'''</span>
<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">* '''l e t  t h e  p a r a d i s e  l o v e  y o u'''</span>
<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">* '''i n  y o u r  n a m e  a  m a u s o l e u m'''</span>
<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">* '''o p e n  y o u r  m i n d'''</span>
<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">* '''a s  i f  f a l l e n  d o w n , a  g i f t  o f  t h e  d i v i n e'''</span>
<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">* '''f e a s t  o n  t h e i r  c o r p s e'''</span>

Additional inscriptions cover sections of the castle walls in unfamiliar and possibly non-human languages. Even when fragments seem momentarily comprehensible, the castle’s persistent psychic influence triggers disorientation, nausea, and cognitive disruption — rendering most wanderers incapable of sustained focus or interpretation.

{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
=<div style="font-family:Avenir; text-align: center;"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">'''The Silver Gate'''</span></div>=
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
<div style="font-family:Avenir; background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25); border:3px solid #D96CBE; box-shadow: 0px 0px 7px #C8509B; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em">
''"I cannot go any further. A vast silver gate stands before me, barring the way to <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''b e a u t y'''</span>. <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''I'''</span> gaze at it, unmoving, unyielding. A sorrow rises within me — I ache to pass through, to follow <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''i t .'''</span> Suddenly, I am unable to breathe. It's as though oxygen itself has been erased from existence. What is this? Perhaps it is the toll required for crossing into '''g r a n d n e s s'''.Time slips by, and I <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''<s>d i e</s> t r a n s c e n d'''</span> in the grip of suffocation. And then — I awaken. The Silver Gate stands open. As I step forward, I glimpse <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''w h o   s h i n e s   b r i g h t   a s   a   t h o u s a n d   s u n s'''."''</span>
</div>
{{Blurimage|file=Silver gate 882.jpg|caption=A close-up photograph taken of The Silver Gate. The image is slightly distorted by the level’s influence.}}
The Silver Gate is a massive metallic portal embedded within the wall of the Golden Castle, measuring approximately 5 by 5 meters. Its surface is adorned with intricate, otherworldly engravings that resist interpretation. Notably, prolonged attempts to breathe while gazing directly at the gate result in sudden and intense suffocation — a phenomenon still unexplained. 

Eventually, wanderers <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''<s>t r a n s c e n d</s>'''</span> lose consciousness from the severe lack of oxygen. When they awaken, the Silver Gate has mysteriously opened, granting passage into the castle’s enigmatic interior. Notably, groups that enter together often find themselves separated once inside, as if the castle itself reshapes their paths. . 

The level now reaches its most perilous stage. If you find yourself here, <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''<s>A M A L G A M A T E W I T H T H E M A U S O L E U M</s></span> turn back without hesitation and return to The Grass.''' An exit will manifest, but beware: the level’s hypnotic influence may erase your memory of it. If your mind remains clear, '''move as far away from The Silver Gate as possible''' before retreating. 

Passing through the Silver Gate brings the wanderer into '''The Corridor''' — the last documented area within Level 882.

{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
=<div style="font-family:Avenir; text-align: center;"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">'''The Corridor'''</span></div>=
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
'''The Corridor''' marks a point of no return. Once crossed, reemergence into previous areas — including The Grass — becomes impossible by known means.

<div style="font-family:Avenir; background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25); border:3px solid #D96CBE; box-shadow: 0px 0px 7px #C8509B; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em">
''"There are no gilded chambers here, no thrones of diamond or halls of splendor. Instead, I stand in a narrow corridor, swallowed by darkness. The Silver Gate closes behind me — sealing out all light. I long for the meadows I left behind, for the ever-dawning sky, for the <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''s t a r s . . .'''</span> This place feels profane beside the <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''p a r a d i s e'''</span> I abandoned. I am alone now, adrift in my own thoughts — until something flickers in the distance. It stirs. It calls <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''— i t . I t   w a n t s   m e   t o   f o l l o w ,   t o   r e a c h   p a r a d i s e . . ."</span>'''''
</div>
{{Blurimage|file=TheCorridor 882.jpg|caption=Photograph of The Corridor: complete darkness stretches in all directions, with only a faint, distant light barely visible ahead — origin unknown.|align=left}}
'''The Corridor''' is a narrow, lightless passage that appears to stretch endlessly. Due to its anomalous properties, all conventional light sources fail within this space, leaving wanderers in complete darkness. Mental deterioration occurs rapidly; most who enter fall quickly into madness. Those few who have escaped credit their survival to the consumption of large quantities of almond water, which seems to preserve cognitive stability to a limited extent. Nevertheless, prolonged exposure inflicts irreversible psychological harm — survivors emerge <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''r e s h a p e d'''</span> , speaking in disjointed, broken phrases that  <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''h a v e'''</span> clear understanding.

Unsettling sounds — screeches, groans, and faint weeping — echo throughout '''The Corridor''', originating from unseen and possibly non-existent sources. It remains uncertain whether these auditory phenomena are hallucinations brought on by psychic stress or the cries of actual entities. The air is sterile and heavy, while the darkness feels almost material, pressing in on the mind. 

Touching the corridor’s walls, which are soft, damp, and faintly pulsing, carries a severe risk: contact may result in infection by the '''[[Hydrolitis Plague]]''', believed to be the one of the only tangible threats in this section aside from psychological collapse.

After an undefined period, wanderers may abruptly drop through the floor without warning, descending into the final and largely undocumented zone of the level — known as '''The Staircase'''.

Those who survive this transition are invariably rendered mute. Medical evaluations of such individuals have revealed the presence of several subtle and unexplained cranial modifications — described as <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''<s>l o v i n g   a n d   c a r i n g   r e m o d e l i n g</s>'''</span> piercings embedded directly into the brain, though no external injuries or incisions are ever found.

All forms of communication — verbal, written, or electronic — fail completely within '''The Corridor'''. The space severs all external contact, leaving wanderers utterly isolated. Those who survive either find a way to escape… or <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''<s>e m b r a c e   t h e   l o v e   o f   i t</s>'''</span> and are never seen again. 

{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
=<div style="font-family:Avenir; text-align: center;"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">'''Anomalies'''</span></div>=
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
Level 882 harbors a powerful '''info hazard''' — an anomalous force that <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''<s>s h a r e s</s>'''</span>  distorts all information related to its most enigmatic traits. Written accounts are particularly vulnerable; the level actively corrupts them, twisting meaning, redacting truths, or replacing facts with hallucinations.

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''F o l l o w   m y   s a y i n g s .'''

Disregard any passage that appears incoherent, misleading, or inconsistent — it may not be the original text, nor your own thought.

{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
=<div style="font-family:Avenir; text-align: center;"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">'''Survivors'''</span></div>=
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
Several survivors of Level 882 have been discovered across various other levels, often exhibiting signs of extreme psychological compromise. Once partially stabilized—typically through high doses of almond water—they began to describe their experiences in a slow, dreamlike cadence: a <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''l e n t i l y   m e d o l i c   v o i c e'''</span>, speaking only of <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''t h e   c u l m i n a t i o n   o f   a   p a r a d i s e'''</span>. Despite their fractured minds, they could not stop <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''s m i l i n g'''</span>, nor cease <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''m i s s i n g   e d e n'''</span>. Each one urged listeners — again and again — to seek out and embrace <span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''t h e   j o y   o f   a   m a u s o l e u m'''.

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''T h e i r   v o i c e s   r e s o n a t e d   w i t h   a   s u b l i m e   c a l m ,'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''u n t o u c h e d   b y   w o r r y ,   r e l a x e d   b e y o n d   a l l   b e l i e f ,'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''a s   t h o u g h   t h e y   h a d   t o u c h e d   t h e   v e r y   e s s e n c e   o f   p e r f e c t i o n . . .'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''W h y   d o   y o u   s h e d   t e a r s ?'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''W h y   m o u r n   w h a t   w a s   b e s t o w e d ?'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''S h o u l d n ’ t   y o u   b e   f i l l e d   w i t h   j o y ?'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''T h e y   a r e   n o t h i n g   b u t   p u r e   e x u l t a t i o n .'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''T h e y   l o n g   f o r   m y   r e t u r n ,   p a i n f u l l y   r e g r e t t i n g   t h e   m o m e n t   t h e y   f l e d   m y   e m b r a c e .'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''**T h e y   r e g r e t   t h e i r   n a I v e t y ,  **'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''a n d   m o u r n   t h e   c h o i c e   t o   n e v e r   c o m e   b a c k ,'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''t o   s e e   m e   b e s t o w   w h a t   t h e y   c o u l d   n e v e r   a t t a i n —'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''w h a t   y o u   t o o k   f r o m   t h e m .'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''W h a t  y o u  S E L F I S H L Y  t o o k f r o m t h e m .'''</span>

{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
=<div style="font-family:Avenir; text-align: center;"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">'''The Staircase'''</span></div>=
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''Y o u   d e s i r e   t o   k n o w   a b o u t   t h e   s t a i r c a s e ?'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''T r y   t o   u n d e r s t a n d   w h a t   y o u   a r e n ’ t   e v e n   a b l e   t o   s t a r t   t o   c o m p r e h e n d .'''</span>

<div style="font-family:Avenir; background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25); border:3px solid #D96CBE; box-shadow: 0px 0px 7px #C8509B; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em">
<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''“A s   I   a p p r o a c h e d   t o   t h e   l i g h t ,   a   s p i r a l i n g   s t a i r c a s e   u n f u r l e d   a b o v e   a n d   b e l o w .'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''I   k n e w   t h i s   w a s   w h a t   I   s o u g h t.'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''A s   I   a s c e n d e d ,   a   n u m b n e s s   a n d   d e l i c a t e   f a i r n e s s   c a r r i e d   m e —   a   b r i e f   g l i m p s e   o f   t h e   D I V I N E .'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''P e r f e c t i o n ,   b e a u t y .   A l l   w a s   w o r t h   i t .'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''A t   t h e   s u m m i t ,   I   b e h o l d e d   a   w o o d e n   d o o r . . .”'''</span>
</div>
{{Blurimage|file=The Staircase 882.jpg|caption=''<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">Extend above and below — what you see might be what you bring.</span>''}}
<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''E x t e n d i n g   a b o v e   a n d   b e l o w —'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''t h i s   s t a i r c a s e   i s   a   p a s s a g e   t o w a r d s   p e r f e c t i o n .'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''T o   c h o o s e   t o   a s c e n d   i s   t o   s e t   f o r t h   o n   t h e   p a t h   o f   d i v i n i t y .'''
</span>
<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''T o   r e g r e t   o r   t o   r e t r e a t ,   t o   d e s c e n d ,   i s   t o   s u r r e n d e r   t o   u n w o r t h i n e s s .'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''A M A L G A M A T E W I T H T H E M A U S O L E U M,'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''A M A U S O L E U M O F E M E R A L D G R E E N.'''</span>

<span style="color:gold;font-family: IM Fell DW Pica, serif">'''B E G F O R M E R C Y F R O M T H E S T A R S,'''</span>

